HEADWORD: Fossores
<hw>Fos*so"res</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>fossor<?/</ets> digger, fr. <ets>fodere</ets> to dig.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of hymenopterous insects including the
sand wasps. They excavate cells in earth, where they deposit their eggs,
with the bodies of other insects for the food of the young when
hatched.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Fossoria</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fossoria</ent>⟦br⟧
